Adam Owens: Concerns over 'legal high' legislation a year on from teenager's death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The mother of a teenager who died after taking so-called legal high drugs has said "everyday's a struggle" a year on from his death.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
13 April 2016 Last updated at 22:40 BST
Adele Wallace also told BBC News NI's Lisa McAlister she was concerned there is not enough help in Northern Ireland for "kids with addictions".
